        "output": "{'id': 'res_005', 'name': 'Emma Walsh', 'yoe_react': 4, 'yoe_python': 3, 'education': 'BS Computer Science, Cornell University (2019). Cornell College of Engineering, GPA 3.5. Coursework: Operating Systems, Compilers, Distributed Systems, Machine Learning.', 'highlights': 'Senior Software Engineer at Notion (2023-present), payments and billing team. Previously Software Engineer at Brex (2019-2023, 4 years), where she shipped the merchant analytics dashboard from prototype to 50K MAU. Strong React + TypeScript practitioner; introduced TanStack Query as the data layer standard across the eng org. Comfortable with Python for data tooling and internal scripts. Mentored 2 junior engineers, both promoted under her tenure. Public speaker at React Summit 2024. Looking for a senior role with more ownership of architecture decisions and a path to staff IC. Available within 6 weeks.'}",
